### Use underscore prefix for private variables in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/guides/Expo JavaScript Style Guide.md

Shows the convention for marking instance variables and module-internal variables as private using an underscore prefix. This communicates private intent while maintaining accessibility for debugging and testing purposes.

```javascript
// CORRECT
class Counter {
  _currentNumber = 0;
  getNextNumber() { ... }
}
```

```javascript
// CORRECT
export default function prettyPrintAll(values) {
  for (let value of values) {
    _prettyPrint(value);
  }
}

function _prettyPrint(value) { ... }
```

