### React component with Expo style conventions in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/guides/Expo JavaScript Style Guide.md

Complete example of a React component demonstrating multiple Expo code style conventions including private method naming with underscore prefix, const/let usage, PropTypes definition, and proper import organization.

```javascript
import Expo from 'expo';
import PropTypes from 'prop-types';
import React from 'react';
import { StyleSheet, Text } from 'react-native';

import Log from '../log/Log';
import Colors from '../style/Colors';

export default class GreetingText extends React.PureComponent {
  static propTypes = {
    greeting: PropTypes.string.isRequired,
    ...Text.propTypes
  };

  componentDidUpdate() {
    Log.info('The greeting was re-rendered');
  }

  render() {
    let { greeting, style, ...props } = this.props;
    return (
      <Text {...props} onPress={this._handlePress} style={[styles.greeting, style]}>
        {greeting}
      </Text>
    );
  }

  _handlePress = event => {
    alert('Congratulations!');
  };
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  greeting: {
    color: Colors.energetic,
    fontSize: 30
  }
});
```

