### Implementing Root Layout Authentication with Expo Router

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/router/basics/common-navigation-patterns.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to use `Stack.Protected` in the root layout (`_layout.tsx`) to guard routes based on the user's authentication status. It conditionally renders protected routes for logged-in users (e.g., `(tabs)`, `modal`) and authentication-related routes for logged-out users (e.g., `sign-in`, `create-account`). The `useAuthState` hook is used to determine the `isLoggedIn` status.

```tsx
import { Stack } from 'expo-router';
import { useAuthState } from '@/utils/authState';

export default function RootLayout() {
  const { isLoggedIn } = useAuthState();

  return (
    <Stack>
      <Stack.Protected guard={isLoggedIn}>
        <Stack.Screen name="(tabs)" />
        <Stack.Screen name="modal" />
      </Stack.Protected>

      <Stack.Protected guard={!isLoggedIn}>
        <Stack.Screen name="sign-in" />
        <Stack.Screen name="create-account" />
      </Stack.Protected>
    </Stack>
  );
}
```

