### Implement Protected Tabs in Expo Router

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/router/advanced/protected.mdx

This snippet shows how to use `Tabs.Protected` to conditionally render tab screens based on a user's login status. Routes within `guard={true}` are protected for logged-in users, while `guard={false}` protects routes for logged-out users.

```tsx
import { Tabs } from 'expo-router';

const isLoggedIn = false;

export default function TabLayout() {
  return (
    <Tabs>
      <Tabs.Screen name="index" options={{ tabBarLabel: 'Home' }} />
      <Tabs.Protected guard={isLoggedIn}>
        <Tabs.Screen name="private" options={{ tabBarLabel: 'Private' }} />
        <Tabs.Screen name="profile" options={{ tabBarLabel: 'Profile' }} />
      </Tabs.Protected>

      <Tabs.Protected guard={!isLoggedIn}>
        <Tabs.Screen name="login" options={{ tabBarLabel: 'Login' }} />
      </Tabs.Protected>
    </Tabs>
  );
}
```

