### Handle Rest Route Parameters as String Array in Expo Router

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/router/reference/url-parameters.mdx

This snippet illustrates how to type route parameters that use the rest syntax (`...everything`) as a string array. It demonstrates accessing individual segments from the array in a React Native component, useful for dynamic multi-segment paths.

```tsx
import { Text } from 'react-native';
import { useLocalSearchParams } from 'expo-router';

export default function Route() {
  const { everything } = useLocalSearchParams<{
    /* @info <b>everything</b> will be an array of path segments, even if there's only one */
    everything: string[];
    /* @end */
  }>();
  const user = everything[0];

  return <Text>User: {user}</Text>;
}

// Given the URL: `/evanbacon/123`
// The following is returned: { everything: ["evanbacon", "123"] }
```

